,Recommended,487770,24420955,"Posted: 20 July, 2016",all,wakasm,"For what it is worth, this game is a nice distraction in VR.What it does well:Haslocal Leaderboards, Friend Leaderboards, and Global Leaderboards (so that any guest can get their initials in the game and compete with you arcade style)Very simple gameplay, with 4 modes:  Easy, Hard, Paper Airplanes through hoops, and garbage in garbage cansAchievements are fair but hard.  Very doable in a few hours, although the Hard Achievement will take a lot of practiceAddictive Repeative Gameplay loopGreat graphics for what it is+2 points for going on fire!What it does poorly:Ball physics are not like a real ball (you can't really put backspin on the ball)The weight of the balls feel off at first... but you get used to it.  The weight makes it hard to put a high arc on the ball.  If you have ever played the Wii Sports basketball game, I am not sure waht they did differently, but that mode felt more right than this as far as feeling like you shooting basketballs with a sense of real motion.  If you can get past the ""realism"" factor though, and learn the physics of the game... it's still funHard modes are mostly easier if you play underhand than overhand because of the limits of VROverall, this was a great addition to my VR library, and I go back to it often enough to try and beat achievements and/or beat my own highscores.  When people try VR, this is a great one to break out if they like sports and/or if they like trying to beat scores.   For wahtever reason, everyone really likes the garbage can mode the most.As a sidenote to other developers of VR, local leaderboards are a must."
